### Conclusion
- Racially based discourse on the "Hindu problem" has many roots.
- Vancouver civic officials sought Dominion intervention to halt the increase in South Asian immigration.
- Popular associations of South Asians with plague validated biological arguments for South Asian exclusion.
American immigration officials associated new arrivals with disease and physical weakness.

